280 g Chicken Thighs
1 unit(s) Lime
3 tbsp Guacamole
1 unit(s) Radish
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
113 g Spring Mix
56 g Croutons
1 unit(s) Tomato
2 tbsp Apricot Spread
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Zest, then juice lime.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Add chicken, lime zest and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside.

Cut radish into 1/4-inch rounds.
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Pan-fry until golden, 2-3 min per side, then transfer chicken to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
Brush apricot spread over pork chops.
Roast in the middle of the oven until cooked through, 6-8 min.**

Add lime juice, ranch dressing and guacamole to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.

When the chicken thighs are almost done, add spring mix, tomatoes, radishes and croutons to the large bowl with dressing.
Toss to combine.

Thinly slice chicken.
Divide salad between plates. Top with chicken.

If you've opted to get chicken thighs, prep and cook them in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook the pork chops.